flowRoot.flowPara: Windowed state allows for quickly switching between multiple windows.
Maximized window make maximal use of the screen estate, while keeping all controls (chrome) exposed. GNOME3 apps launch maximized by default (see below for exceptions).
Chrome is UNDESIRED. Content has all the focus. Entering fullscreen mode is an explicit user action.
Chrome can be toggled on temporarily by tapping on touch, or by moving the mouse. It fades away after some time of inactivity.
The top bar shows up as an overlay along with controls.
